{{head|fr|conjunction}}

# [[since]], [[because]]
#: {{ux|fr|'''''Puisqu'''’il ne sera pas de retour avant cinq heures, je propose que nous commencions sans lui.|'''Since''' he will not be back before 5 o’clock, I suggest we begin without him.}}
#* {{quote-text|fr|year=2018|author=Zaz|title=Qué vendrá
|passage='''Puisque''' nous sommes ici sans savoir ce qui nous attend un peu plus tard, laisser parler mon instinct me guérit.|t='''Since''' we're here without knowing what awaits us a little bit later, letting my instinct[s] speak heals me.}}

====Usage notes====
* '''{{m|fr||Puisque}}''' is elided to {{m|fr|puisqu'}} before a vowel.
* Verbs subordinate to '''{{m|fr||puisque}}''' do not traditionally take the [[subjunctive]], but such usage is sometimes encountered in the speech of native Francophones.
